                    </div>
                    <span>I found this book to wander around in circles.  Your best bet would be go right to the source - read "The Four Agreements" by Don Miguel Ruiz himself, and you will find the simplicity of his readings more beneficial - it's direct and intertwined with relations of the agreements with all aspects of life - home, friends, work - it's a wonderful philosophy, so to speak.  Then read any of his other books and you will be pleasantly enlightened.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Many people have already mis-judged.</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>4</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
